.nh
.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-provision-ios - Prepare this macOS node to run iOS builds


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel provision ios [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Configure code-signing and tooling so this node can run IOS_BUILD jobs.

.PP
Steps performed:
  - Create/unlock a dedicated build keychain and set its partition list.
  - Import a distribution certificate (.p12) when --cert is given.
  - Install provisioning profiles into the user's Provisioning Profiles dir.
  - Verify Xcode command-line tools are installed (hint to install if missing).

.PP
Sensitive material is supplied as paths/params and never hardcoded. Use
--dry-run to print every command without touching the keychain.

.PP
Examples:
  # Print the plan without executing anything (no certs needed)
  citadel provision ios --dry-run \\
    --keychain citadel-build.keychain-db --keychain-password "$KC_PW"

.PP
# Real run: import a cert and install a profile
  citadel provision ios \\
    --keychain citadel-build.keychain-db --keychain-password "$KC_PW" \\
    --cert ./dist.p12 --cert-password "$CERT_PW" \\
    --profile ./app.mobileprovision


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--cert\fP=""
	Path to a distribution certificate (.p12) to import

.PP
\fB--cert-password\fP=""
	Export password for the .p12 certificate

.PP
\fB--dry-run\fP[=false]
	Print the provisioning commands without executing them

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for ios

.PP
\fB--keychain\fP="citadel-build.keychain-db"
	Dedicated build keychain to create/unlock

.PP
\fB--keychain-password\fP=""
	Password for the build keychain (required)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=[]
	Path to a .mobileprovision profile to install (repeatable)

.PP
\fB--profiles-dir\fP=""
	Override the provisioning profiles install directory


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-provision(1)\fP
